1943;;Hostages;;American;;Frank Tuttle;;Luise Rainer, William Bendix;;war;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hostages_(1943_film);;A group of 26 Czechoslovakian citizens are jailed as hostages by the Gestapo until the supposed killer of a Nazi officer – who actually committed suicide – is turned in. The hostages include the leader of the underground resistance movement (William Bendix), whose cover is that of an apparently ignorant washroom attendant in the nightclub where the victim was last seen alive.